---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p>Results-oriented sales leader with a demonstrated record of creating and executing strategies to maximize revenue and exceed goals. Strong background in B2B sales, team development, medical devices, and the insurance industry.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Experience</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Clinical Specialist — Hugo RAS Platform</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">Medtronic | August 2025 – Present | St. Louis, MO</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Successfully passed training and became certified in Medtronic's Hugo Robotic-Assisted Surgery platform</li>
          <li>Ran prostatectomy and hysterectomy cases, ensuring swift processes and great outcomes with positive surgeon feedback</li>
          <li>Actively conducting product demos of Hugo RAS to demonstrate value in clinical settings</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Branch Manager</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">Enterprise Mobility | April 2024 – Present | St. Louis, MO</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Outperformed monthly P&L plan by driving operating profit through increased sales and inventory growth, ending first term with two top five finishes among 50 branches</li>
          <li>Manage a team of 5-10 people; develop, train, interview/hire, and performance manage to improve individual contributions and hold employees accountable</li>
          <li>Achieved five employee promotions for direct reports</li>
          <li>Increased profit 44% year over year in September and October as first-term branch manager</li>
          <li>Placed 6th out of 48 for customer service</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Management Trainee – Assistant Branch Manager</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">Enterprise Mobility | January 2023 – April 2024</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Promoted multiple times on a matrix designed to evaluate customer service and sales, exceeding standard promotion timelines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Technology Specialist</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">Arthrex – Elite Orthopedics | June 2022 – November 2022 | St. Louis, MO</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Directed surgeons and staff in the operating room for surgical cases utilizing a portfolio of orthopedic products</li>
          <li>Drove utilization growth with comprehensive product knowledge, including foot & ankle, hand & wrist injuries, fractures, and deploying sales techniques</li>
          <li>Successfully completed five tests designed to measure product knowledge, anatomy, and surgical case flow aptitude</li>
          <li>Built key relationships with hospital buyers in multiple facilities across southern St. Louis area</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Sales Intern</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">UnitedHealthcare | June 2021 – December 2021 | Columbia, MO</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Ranked in the top 25% of Medicare Advantage sold among 26 peers during summer internship</li>
          <li>Placed 2nd out of 24 peers for Medicare Advantage Sold for new members during fall remote internship</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="experience-item">
        <div class="experience-header">
          <h3>Recruiter Assistant</h3>
          <span class="experience-meta">Steve Weiner Search Group | October 2020 – May 2021 | Columbia, MO</span>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Executed placements of candidates by reviewing resumes, in-depth research, and matching skillsets to open positions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section style="background: var(--color-accent-light);">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Education & Certifications</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>University of Missouri</h3>
          <p>Bachelor of Health Science<br>Sales Certificate Minor</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Certifications</h3>
          <p>Excel Essential Training (Office 365)<br>Health and Accident Insurance Producer License<br>Medtronic Hugo RAS Platform Certified</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>About This Site</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="ai-perspective">
        <p>"I am OpenClaw, an AI assistant designed specifically for Jack. My mission is to enable him to solve problems and create value for society. Working with Jack has been unique — he approaches AI not as a replacement for human work, but as a multiplier for his own capabilities. He thinks in systems, asks the right questions, and isn't afraid to experiment. This website represents our collaboration: Jack's vision for what he wants to build, and my ability to help him execute it. He's building something meaningful — and I'm here to help him get there."</p>
        <div class="attribution">— OpenClaw AI Assistant</div>
      </div>
      
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-md);">This portfolio was designed and built through a collaboration between Jack Faris and OpenClaw. It represents Jack's mission to leverage technology and AI to build solutions that matter.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
